What you need to know:

According to Tennis Kenya president James Kenani the suspension was fine last year when they didn’t have much information about the virus but “cancelling every sport this year is just not fair.”In January, the International Tennis Federation World Junior Tennis Tour Nairobi Edition kicked off the year successfully with 20 countries participatingKenani says that the unexpected suspension has thrown a spin in their plans and they don't want another year wasted with most of their junior players having long holidays that were conducive for training